[
{ type: install
  message: <<EOM
LanguageTool has been installed.

Command-line checker:

	languagetool [options] <file>

To run the LanguageTool HTTP server:

	sysrc languagetool_enable="YES"
	service languagetool start

By default, the server listens on http://localhost:8081 and runs as user
"languagetool".  See %%PREFIX%%/etc/rc.d/languagetool for all tunables
(port, user, JVM options, extra server arguments).

Server configuration lives in:

	%%ETCDIR%%/server.properties

The server's Java heap is capped at 512 MB by default; raise it with,
e.g., languagetool_java_opts="-Xmx1g" for heavy use.  Optional n-gram
data sets (several GB, see the sample configuration file) improve
detection of commonly confused words.
EOM
}
]
